## üì¶ Reset `main` to a Single Commit (Clean History)

This guide explains how to wipe the entire commit history of your `main` branch and start fresh with a single commit, keeping the current project state.

‚ö†Ô∏è **Warning:** This rewrites history! Anyone else working with this repository will need to re-clone or reset their local branches.

---

### üõ†Ô∏è Steps

```bash
# 1Ô∏è‚É£ Switch to the main branch
git checkout main

# 2Ô∏è‚É£ Create a new orphan branch (no history)
git checkout --orphan temp-main

# 3Ô∏è‚É£ Stage all files
git add -A

# 4Ô∏è‚É£ Create a new initial commit
git commit -m "Initial commit with current project state"

# 5Ô∏è‚É£ Delete the old main branch
git branch -D main

# 6Ô∏è‚É£ Rename temp-main to main
git branch -m main

# 7Ô∏è‚É£ Force push the new main to remote
git push --force origin main
